It seems it is not possible to disable vendor prefixes for emmet or css autocomplete
type "transi" + tab
and you'll get:
    -webkit-transition: prop time;
    -o-transition: prop time;
    transition: prop time;
This feature should be optional, some people may delegate the vendor-prefixes to postcss for example.

I just checked on master, the `ts` scope is no longer seems to be applied to vanilla js (which is probably a good thing). But the dark and light (Visual Studio) themes are missing some important js styles that are scoped with `ts`, most notably the coloring of `function` and `var`:

```
.monaco-editor.vs-dark .token.var.storage.type.ts {
    color: #569CD6;
}
.monaco-editor.vs-dark .token.storage.type.ts {
    color: #569CD6;
}
```

